ecutive coaching institute strategy  management marketing strategy in the digital age strategy in competitive markets negotiation and influence executive decision making venture capital executive program product management certificate of business excellence calendar programs for organizations custom programs innovation acceleration group our faculty the berkeley experience why berkeley insights testimonials enter your keywords homa bahrami senior lecturer haas school of business in today’s fluid world the essential leadership quality is continual adaptability to new realities this is called superflexibility dr homa bahrami is the faculty director for the new manager boot camp for engineers  scientists boot camp for experienced leaders and several custom programs for leading global and technology companies including adobe statoil visa plantronics and cepheid she is a senior lecturer at the haas school of business university of california berkeley management  organization group and an international educator advisor board member and author specializing in enterprise flexibility and dynamic leadership in global knowledgebased industries she is the coauthor of a major textbook with harold leavitt stanford university managerial psychology managing behavior in organizations published by the university of chicago press and translated into many languages her latest book “superflexibility for knowledge enterprises” second edition published by springer coauthored with stuart evans carnegie mellon university focuses on practical approaches for strategizing organizing and leading knowledge enterprises based on their collective experience and field research on dynamic adaptation and enterprise flexibility in silicon valley homa serves on the boards of directors of two public technology companies where she is a member of the audit and compensation committees and chairs the governance committee she works with boards and executive teams on enterprise transformation team alignment leadership development organizing for flexibility  agility and addressing scaling  growth challenges in tech companies homa bahrami serves as faculty director for the following custom programs • adobe alumni program • avaya global management development program • boot camp for haas unit leaders • cepheid directors global leadership program • cepheid global leadership development program • cepheid new manager boot camp program • hr strategy forum • leading change at deckers brands program • leading adobe program • plantronics management development program • statoil pe program  cohort  • statoil project director academy program • superflexibility program • technicolor • total sa leadership program • visa womens leadership diversity program • visas executive edge program   programs for individuals new manager boot camp boot camp for experienced leadersthe innovative organizationacademic background phd organizational behavior aston university united kingdom msc industrial administration aston university united kingdom ba with honors sociology  social administration hull university  united kingdom publications  media videos  homa bahrami lessons from silicon valley watch video ways leaders can improve team performance watch video a look inside the new manager boot camp watch video boot camp for experienced leaders watch video bahrami  modes of adaptation watch video advice to leaders watch video intermune case study trailer watch video ucsf diabetes center case study trailer watch video view more books  superflexibility for knowledge enterprises a toolkit for dynamic adaptation view book managerial psychology managing behavior in organizations view book view more papers  articles  superflexibility  thriving in a world of constant change view paper effective leaders learn to change it up view paper silicon valley adaptation modes view paper tools to diagnose team health view paper strategic management in hightechnology firms an exploratory study view paper superflexibility